      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/26.2?lang=spa#1" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 26:2</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/28.13?lang=spa#12" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 28:13</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote3-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote3-02285_002_004">3.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/eph/2.19-20?lang=spa#18" target="_blank">Efesios 2:19&ndash;20</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote4-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote4-02285_002_004">4.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/eph/4.11-13?lang=spa#10" target="_blank">Efesios 4:11&ndash;13</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote5-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote5-02285_002_004">5.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/1-cor/12.31?lang=spa#30" target="_blank">1 Corintios 12:31</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/ether/12.11?lang=spa#10" target="_blank">&Eacute;ter 12:11</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote6-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote6-02285_002_004">6.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/34.32-33?lang=spa#31" target="_blank">Alma 34:32&ndash;33</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote7-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote7-02285_002_004">7.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/rev/14.6?lang=spa#5" target="_blank">Apocalipsis 14:6</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote8-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote8-02285_002_004">8.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/john/3.3,7?lang=spa#2" target="_blank">Juan 3:3, 7</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.25?lang=spa#24" target="_blank">Mos&iacute;ah 27:25</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/5.49?lang=spa#48" target="_blank">Alma 5:49</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/7.14?lang=spa#13" target="_blank">Alma 7:14</a>; <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.59?lang=spa#58" target="_blank">Mois&eacute;s 6:59</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote9-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote9-02285_002_004">9.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">La familia: Una proclamaci&oacute;n para el mundo, <span class="emphasis">Liahona</span>, octubre de 1998, p&aacute;g. 24.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote10-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote10-02285_002_004">10.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/ps/127.3?lang=spa#2" target="_blank">Salmos 127:3</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote11-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote11-02285_002_004">11.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/42.8?lang=spa#7" target="_blank">Alma 42:8</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote12-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote12-02285_002_004">12.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/pgp/moses/1.39?lang=spa#38" target="_blank">Mois&eacute;s 1:39</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote13-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote13-02285_002_004">13.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/14.7?lang=spa#6" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 14:7</a>; v&eacute;ase tambi&eacute;n <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/15.9?lang=spa#8" target="_blank">3 Nefi 15:9</a>. En el Libro de Morm&oacute;n se explica con m&aacute;s detalle el car&aacute;cter condicional de este gran don. Declara que &ldquo;deb&eacute;is seguir adelante con firmeza en Cristo, teniendo un fulgor perfecto de esperanza y amor por Dios y por todos los hombres. Por tanto, <span class="emphasis">si</span> march&aacute;is adelante, deleit&aacute;ndoos en la palabra de Cristo, y persever&aacute;is hasta el fin, he aqu&iacute;, as&iacute; dice el Padre: Tendr&eacute;is la vida eterna&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/31.20?lang=spa#19" target="_blank">2 Nefi 31:20</a>; cursiva agregada).</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote14-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote14-02285_002_004">14.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/131.1-3?lang=spa#0" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 131:1–3</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote15-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote15-02285_002_004">15.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.57-58?lang=spa#56" target="_blank">Mois&eacute;s 6:57&ndash;58</a>. Obs&eacute;rvese tambi&eacute;n la siguiente ense&ntilde;anza del rey Benjam&iacute;n: &ldquo;Ni permitir&eacute;is que vuestros hijos anden hambrientos ni desnudos, ni consentir&eacute;is que quebranten las leyes de Dios, ni que contiendan y ri&ntilde;an unos con otros y sirvan al diablo, que es el maestro del pecado&hellip; Mas les ense&ntilde;ar&eacute;is a andar por las v&iacute;as de la verdad y la seriedad; les ense&ntilde;ar&eacute;is a amarse mutuamente y a servirse el uno al otro&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/4.14-15?lang=spa#13" target="_blank">Mos&iacute;ah 4:14&ndash;15</a>).</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote16-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote16-02285_002_004">16.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/deut/6.7?lang=spa#6" target="_blank">Deuteronomio 6:7</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote17-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote17-02285_002_004">17.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/93.40?lang=spa#39" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 93:40</a>. El Se&ntilde;or tambi&eacute;n dijo: &ldquo;Ense&ntilde;ar&aacute;n a sus hijos a orar y a andar rectamente delante del Se&ntilde;or&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/68.28?lang=spa#27" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 68:28</a>).</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote18-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote18-02285_002_004">18.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">As&iacute; se lo ense&ntilde;&oacute; Pablo a Timoteo: &ldquo;Persiste t&uacute; en lo que has aprendido y te persuadiste, sabiendo de qui&eacute;n has aprendido&hellip; Desde la ni&ntilde;ez has sabido las Sagradas Escrituras, las cuales te pueden hacer sabio para la salvaci&oacute;n por la fe que es en Cristo Jes&uacute;s&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/2-tim/3.14-15?lang=spa#13" target="_blank">2 Timoteo 3:14&ndash;15</a>).</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote19-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote19-02285_002_004">19.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/ex/20.12?lang=spa#11" target="_blank">&Eacute;xodo 20:12</a>. Recuerden aquel proverbio dedicado a los padres: &ldquo;Instruye al ni&ntilde;o en su camino, y aun cuando fuere viejo no se apartar&aacute; de &eacute;l&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/prov/22.6?lang=spa#5" target="_blank">Proverbios 22:6</a>).</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote20-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote20-02285_002_004">20.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/121.41-43?lang=spa#40" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 121:41–43</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote21-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote21-02285_002_004">21.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/128.15?lang=spa#14" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 128:15</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote22-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote22-02285_002_004">22.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/128.18?lang=spa#17" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 128:18</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote23-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote23-02285_002_004">23.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/137.9?lang=spa#8" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 137:9</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote24-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote24-02285_002_004">24.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/130.20-21?lang=spa#19" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 130:20–21</a>; v&eacute;ase tambi&eacute;n Rudger Clawson, en <span class="emphasis">Conference Report,</span> octubre de 1917, p&aacute;g. 29: Joseph F. Smith, en <span class="emphasis">Deseret News, </span>1&ordm; de mayo de 1878, p&aacute;g. 2; Richard G. Scott, &ldquo;El gozo de vivir el gran plan de felicidad&rdquo;, <span class="emphasis">Liahona,</span> enero de 1997, p&aacute;g. 84.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote25-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote25-02285_002_004">25.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/86.9,11?lang=spa#8" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 86:9, 11</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote26-02285_002_004"><a name="-02285_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote26-02285_002_004">26.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/12.24?lang=spa#23" target="_blank">Alma 12:24</a>.</p>
			</li> </ol>
                                            
